'''[[Public speaking|Pure]] speech''' in United States law is the communication of ideas through spoken or written words or through conduct limited in form to that necessary to convey the idea. It is distinguished from [[symbolic speech]] or "speech plus," which involves conveying an idea or message through behavior. Pure speech is accorded the highest degree of protection under the [[First Amendment to the U.S. Constitution]].
